columns.text:
The value for the DOL is needed in the first question. We can recall that DOL can be solved in two ways depending on the given. Since the fixed cost and the operating cashflow is given, then we can use this:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{DOL}&=1+\dfrac{\text{FC}}{\text{OCF}}
\end{aligned}$$

In the next question, since we are dealing with changes in values, we can use the second formula for DOL:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{DOL}&=\dfrac{\Delta \text{OCF}}{\Delta \text{Q}}
\end{aligned}$$
